    "title": "Kesari Tours South Asia Partners is Hiring: Guest Relations Manager (Junior)",
    "description": "Grow your career with Kesari Tours South Asia Partners! We are hiring a Guest Relations Manager for our Mysuru team. Be part of a workplace that celebrates innovation, diversity, and performance.\n\nAbout Kesari Tours South Asia Partners:\nKesari Tours South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure compliance with FSSAI, health, and safety regulations\n• Deliver exceptional guest experiences in line with brand standards\n• Develop and maintain relationships with corporate clients\n• Handle guest complaints and resolve issues promptly\n• Conduct regular guest satisfaction surveys and implement improvements\n• Monitor F&B service quality and maintain hygiene standards\n• Plan and execute banquets, events, and MICE functions\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Crisis Management\n• Proficiency in Revenue Management\n• Proficiency in Customer Relations\n• Proficiency in GDS Systems\n• Proficiency in OTA Management\n• Proficiency in F&B Service\n• Proficiency in HACCP\n• Proficiency in Event Management\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Mysuru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Kesari Tours South Asia Partners!",
